Task.Name: Project Management (PM)
Task.Notes: A set of methods and techniques designed to ensure successful delivery projects (large complex projects are often managed by a Project Management Office using this methodology) in a cost-effective, schedule-compressed manner.

Task.Name: Initiating
Task.Notes: The Initiating Stage does the preliminary analysis to define the project objectives and ensures that further project work is authorized.

Task.Name: Develop Project Charter
Task.Notes: The Project Charter is developed to formally authorize a project. The Project Charter contrains the high level definition of the project and the business justification for the project.

Task.Name: Identify Goals and Objectives
Task.Notes: Define the primary goals and objectives for the project.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Goals and Objectives, List of Constraints

Task.Name: Develop Strategies and Plans
Task.Notes: Understand the business organization and its personnel and formulate high level strategies and plans to ensure achievement of objectives.

Task.Name: Research Previous Experience
Task.Notes: Research previous experience with similar projects and with similar technologies and obtain sample materials.

Task.Name: Develop Project Charter
Task.Notes: Develop the Project Charter and present it for approval to proceed with the project.

Task.Name: Develop Preliminary Project Scope Statement
Task.Notes: The preliminary steps necessary to develop the project's goals and objectives and secure commitment to continue the project.

Task.Name: Conduct Planning Workshop
Task.Notes: Conduct an internal planning session to think through all elements of the project, identify the critical success factors, and map out the project approach.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Delivery Approach, Meeting Minutes, Action Items

Task.Name: Document Project Costs and Benefits
Task.Notes: Perform the cost/benefit analysis for the projects. Document the cash flows, (i.e., benefits minus costs). Document the benefits and risks that cannot be assigned a cash value.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Benefit Estimating Worksheets, Cost Estimating Worksheets

Task.Name: Develop High Level Work Breakdown Structure
Task.Notes: Completely identify all of the work to be performed and organize the work into manageable pieces (subprojects).

Task.Name: Conduct Peer Review
Task.Notes: Conduct a peer review session to solicit feedback on the project approach from senior delivery and management personnel from outside the project team.

Task.Name: Prepare Preliminary Project Scope Statement
Task.Notes: Consolidate the preliminary planning material developed into the Preliminary Project Scope Statement

Task.Name: Planning
Task.Notes: The Planning Stage defines the necessary steps to ensure that proper planning is done, during project start-up, before each new phase starts and as part of the change management process

Task.Name: Set Up Project Environment
Task.Notes: Ensure that the fundamental project delivery infrastructure is in place (e.g., work space, standards and procedures, project tools).

Task.Name: Prepare Facilities
Task.Notes: Obtain and furnish work space with the appropriate facilities.

Task.Name: Set Up Project Standards and Procedures
Task.Notes: Define and document the specific standards and procedures to be applied on the project to ensure consistent delivery in accordance with the quality requirements.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Project Standards and Procedures, Standards and Procedures for Team Performance, Standards and Procedures for General Practices, Standards and Procedures for Meetings, Standards and Procedures for Cost/Schedule Management, Standards and Procedures for Org

Task.Name: Set Up Project Management Tools
Task.Notes: Implement the project management tools to be used by the project team to manage performance.

Task.Name: Set Up Project Book
Task.Notes: Collect and store the project's quality and scope control records in a standard, single location to provide familiar, rapid access to key project management information.

Task.Name: Define Scope
Task.Notes: Establish the Project Scope, WBS and Deliverables necessary to ensure that the objectives defined in the Project Charter are met.

Task.Name: Document Scope Management Plan
Task.Notes: The Scope Management Plan defines the degree of rigor to be applied to the project based on it's size, complexity, risk tolerance and organizational importance.

Task.Name: Specify Deliverables and Acceptance Criteria
Task.Notes: Create a clear and unambiguous definition of each deliverable in terms of format, size and quality requirements, and specify the acceptance procedures and acceptance criteria for each deliverable.

Task.Name: Define Scope
Task.Notes: Establish and maintain a common understanding with the customer of the scope of the project.

Task.Name: Document Assumptions
Task.Notes: Maintain an ongoing list of the assumptions on which the estimates and schedules are based.

Task.Name: Develop Project Schedule
Task.Notes: Identify and assign project resources, determine project activity and task dependencies, develop task estimates develop the project schedule.

Task.Name: Build Work Breakdown Structure
Task.Notes: Develop the project structure in terms of detailed phases, activities, tasks, deliverables, and resources.

Task.Name: Develop Resource Plans
Task.Notes: Identify resources (human and other) that will be required to successfully deliver the project

Task.Name: Prepare Project Estimates
Task.Notes: Produce a detailed estimates of the costs and material resources required to deliver each component of the Work Breakdown Structure.

Task.Name: Define Dependencies and Develop Project Schedule
Task.Notes: Define the milestones and phase dates for each component of the Work Breakdown Structure, and identify the dependencies between the work components (the network logic).

Task.Name: Document Assumptions
Task.Notes: Maintain an ongoing list of the assumptions on which the estimates and schedules are based.

Task.Name: Develop Risk Plans
Task.Notes: Identify, analyze and profile project risks,

Task.Name: Document Risk Management Plan
Task.Notes: Describe the methods and procedures to be used to identify, evaluate, and eliminate or minimize project risks.

Task.Name: Identify Risks
Task.Notes: Risk identification identifies the risks which if unmanaged could impact the project.

Task.Name: Analyze Risks
Task.Notes: Qualitative and Quantitative Analysis of a project's risks and impacts. The result is a prioritized list of risks.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Risk Management Action Plan, Risk Management Log

Task.Name: Document Risk Management Plans
Task.Notes: Profile the potential risks to the project by producing specific plans to reduce or eliminate high risk items before they become obstacles to successful project delivery.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Risk Management Action Plan, Risk Management Log

Task.Name: Plan for Quality
Task.Notes: Prepare the way for a quality project.

Task.Name: Document Quality Management Plan
Task.Notes: Establish the baseline against which project quality will be measured and describe the methods and procedures to be used for monitoring and verifying project quality.

Task.Name: Organize Project Resources
Task.Notes: Identify and mobilize a productive and motivated project team.

Task.Name: Develop Organization Structure
Task.Notes: Create an effective and efficient project organization structure.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Organization Structure, Project Organization Chart, Project Management Organization, Project Delivery Organization, Responsibility Assignment Matrix, Mechanisms for Formal Communications

Task.Name: Develop Staffing Plan
Task.Notes: Identify the skills required for each role within the project structure, the person-day estimates and start and end dates for each role.

Task.Name: Develop Procurement Plans
Task.Notes: To understand and document what needs to be purchased/contracted for the project and how the purchasing/contracting is to be done.

Task.Name: Determine Procurement Requirements
Task.Notes: To understand which project components will be delivered with in-house resources and which will have to be procured from outside vendors/suppliers

Task.Name: Define Subcontractor Scope
Task.Notes: Define the scope of work to be accomplished by each project subcontractor.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Acquisition Management Plan, Definition of Project Scope, Statement of Requirements, Statement of Work, Planning Budget, Planning Schedule, Requisition Documents, Statement of Requirements, Definition of Project Scope, Statement of Work

Task.Name: Identify Potential Subcontractors
Task.Notes: To develop and qualify a shortlist of potential subcontractors for the project.

Task.Name: Identify Subcontract Type
Task.Notes: Identify the appropriate type of contract to be used for each identified procurement requirement.

Task.Name: Document Subcontractor Management Plan
Task.Notes: Describe the methods and procedures to be used in subcontracting work.

Task.Name: Develop Financial Plan
Task.Notes: Document the expected cash flow as the basis for monitoring the monthly financial performance of the project.

Task.Name: Prepare Financial Plan
Task.Notes: Translate the estimates and schedule into an expected monthly cash flow as the basis for monitoring the project's financial performance.

Task.Name: Document Assumptions
Task.Notes: Maintain an ongoing list of the assumptions on which the estimates and schedules are based.

Task.Name: Develop Project Support Plans
Task.Notes: Document the Risk, Configuration and Data Management Plans which will be used to define these aspects of the project delivery approach.

Task.Name: Document Communications Management Plan
Task.Notes: Describe the methods and procedures to be used to identify and document the project communications requirements.

Task.Name: Document Configuration Management Plan
Task.Notes: Describe the methods and procedures to be used to establish effective identification, control, accounting, and auditing of controlled items throughout the development life cycle.

Task.Name: Document Data Management Plan
Task.Notes: Describe the methods and procedures to be used to implement and maintain a Data Management System for the identification, acquisition, distribution, delivery, and status reporting of data.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Data Management Plan, Configuration Management Plan

Task.Name: Develop Project Management Plan
Task.Notes: The Project Management Plan contains the results of the Project Planning Phase and provides the definition against which the project will be delivered.

Task.Name: Document Project Management Plan
Task.Notes: Establish the baseline for scope, budget, schedule, and quality, against which project performance is measured and all changes to the project are controlled.

Task.Name: Executing
Task.Notes: Coordinating the people and other resources required to deliver the project

Task.Name: Acquire Project Team
Task.Notes: Assemble, deliver team orientation and assign project responsibilities

Task.Name: Obtain Resources
Task.Notes: Negotiate for resources and prepare action plans to identify any staffing deficiencies.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Staff Rotation Plan, Action Items, Project Team Directory

Task.Name: Conduct Team Orientation
Task.Notes: Provide a formal orientation to the project and build a common understanding within the team.

Task.Name: Assign Responsibilities
Task.Notes: Delegate responsibility for work assignments and witness commitment.

Task.Name: Direct and Manage Project Execution
Task.Notes: Manage the data that supports the project and implement the discipline of configuration management.

Task.Name: Manage Data Items
Task.Notes: Identify, control and report upon the scheduling, publishing and release of all formal data items, and the replacement of obsolete versions, in accordance with the terms of the project plan.

Task.Name: Manage Configuration Items
Task.Notes: Identify, control, and report upon selected baseline items, such as the project description, product specifications and process specifications, which formally define the project.

Task.Name: Manage Process Data
Task.Notes: Collect and maintain a standard set of data on the project's processes, metrics, and lessons learned.

Task.Name: Provide General Office Support
Task.Notes: Provide general office support such as producing correspondence, document production and distribution services, and maintaining files and logs.

Task.Name: Administer Project Security Processes
Task.Notes: Design and implement procedures to ensure adequate project security, including such things as badges, sign-in registers, electronic lock accessibility, and monitoring the security related practices in all project facilities.

Task.Name: Manage Team Performance
Task.Notes: Optimize the performance of team members in achieving project goals.

Task.Name: Provide Team Training
Task.Notes: Provide training to members of the project team (including business and subcontractor personnel) in the project-specific methodology, tools, or technology, as required.

Task.Name: Recognize Success
Task.Notes: Develop and implement means to recognize and reward quality service, creativity, innovation, and success.

Task.Name: Assure Quality
Task.Notes: Monitor the levels of quality being achieved.

Task.Name: Participate in Walk-throughs and Reviews
Task.Notes: Participate in structured walk-throughs and reviews of project deliverables with members of the project team, to represent quality concerns.

Task.Name: Conduct Inspections and Audits
Task.Notes: Conduct inspections and audits to determine the completeness and consistency of processes and deliverables.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Inspection and Audit Reports, Action Items

Task.Name: Conduct Project Reviews
Task.Notes: Review and appraise the project to assess and increase the probability of project success.

Task.Name: Facilitate Continuous Improvement
Task.Notes: Investigate the causes of problems and analyze work operations to identify process improvements and reduce or eliminate failures.

Task.Name: Manage Project Communication
Task.Notes: Develop and maintain a good working relationship with all the project stakeholders by using effective project communications.

Task.Name: Review Progress
Task.Notes: Maintain frequent formal and informal contact with project stakeholders to review progress and maintain open communication.

Task.Name: Contracting with Subcontractors
Task.Notes: Selection and management of any subcontractors required to deliver the project.

Task.Name: Issue Requisition Documents
Task.Notes: Issue the formal requisition documents to prospective subcontractors.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Requisition Documents, Statement of Requirements, Definition of Project Scope, Statement of Work

Task.Name: Evaluate Responses
Task.Notes: Evaluate responses to the formal requisition documents from prospective subcontractors.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Clarification of Requisition Requirements, Bid Evaluations, Confirmation of Preferred Subcontractor, Supplier Quality Assessment

Task.Name: Negotiate Subcontractor Contract
Task.Notes: Negotiate effective contracts with subcontractors and arrange subcontract signing.

Task.Name: Monitoring and Controlling
Task.Notes: Monitoring and measuring the project performance to ensure that the project is on target (on time, on budget meeting expectations).

Task.Name: Monitor and Control Project Work
Task.Notes: Monitor and control contains the project tasks which validate the overall project direction by validating that the project work is progressing according to the plan.

Task.Name: Authorize Work
Task.Notes: Delegate delivery responsibilities for a work package, establish a clear and unambiguous understanding for how the work package is to be delivered, witness commitment, and formally authorize the commencement of work.

Task.Name: Manage Action Items
Task.Notes: Record, communicate and ensure closure on all action items including changes to the contractual baseline, requirements for information, problem reports and service requests, to facilitate effective decision-making within acceptable time frames.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Action Item Reports, Change Request, Change Request Log, Decision Request, Decision Request Log, Information Request, Information Request Log, Fault Report, Fault Report Log, Service Request, Service Request Log, Issue Resolution Request, Issue Log, Accep

Task.Name: Manage Project Records
Task.Notes: Establish, maintain, and dispose of project records in a way that provides adequate access for team members during the project and long-term retention for use in subsequent projects.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Project Book, Staffing Plan, Staff Rotation Plan, Project Team Directory, Project Index

Task.Name: Integrated Change Control
Task.Notes: Maintain a comprehensive, clear, and measurable definition of the project scope and requirements.

Task.Name: Manage Scope
Task.Notes: Establish and maintain a common understanding with the Acceptor of the scope of the project.

Task.Name: Manage Requirements
Task.Notes: Establish and maintain a common understanding with the customer of the requirements that will be addressed by the project.

Task.Name: Control Decisions
Task.Notes: Ensure that the project team is provided with the information and decisions necessary to keep the project on track.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Decision Request, Decision Request Log, Information Request, Information Request Log

Task.Name: Control Changes
Task.Notes: Record and obtain approval for any and every change to the approved project baselines.

Task.Name: Scope Verification
Task.Notes: Scope verification ensures that the project deliverables are formally accepted.

Task.Name: Manage Project Acceptance
Task.Notes: Obtain acceptance of deliverables and final sign-off that the project has been completed.

Task.Name: Schedule Control
Task.Notes: Maintaining the Project Schedule to ensure it remains accurate and current based on approved Change Requests and revised estimates to complete from Project Team Members.

Task.Name: Track Status
Task.Notes: Track detailed progress against each activity and task, re-assess personal commitment, and re-forecast the remaining effort to completion and the expected completion date, on a regular weekly basis.

Task.Name: Maintain Project Schedule
Task.Notes: Perform the appropriate updates to the project schedule to account for current project status, approved project changes and other project issues.

Task.Name: Maintain Work Plans
Task.Notes: Maintain a current and reliable version of the project work plans, based on approved changes and current estimates to completion.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Work Plans, Project Schedules, List of Assumptions, List of Constraints, Detailed Work Breakdown Structure, Financial Plan

Task.Name: Manage Finances
Task.Notes: Manage the monthly cash flow of the project, including the forecasted estimates to complete for the remainder of the project.

Task.Name: Monitor Cost/Schedule Variance
Task.Notes: Analyze cost and schedule variances from plan and implement corrective action.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Project Cost/Schedule Performance Report, Action Items

Task.Name: Control Costs
Task.Notes: Control project costs and expenses so as deliver the project on budget.

Task.Name: Maintain Financial Plan
Task.Notes: Reconcile the project's financial data with the corporate financial system and update the financial estimates to complete for the remainder of the project

Task.Name: Perform Quality Control
Task.Notes: Implement and manage a program to ensure the project quality and implement continual improvement of work operations.

Task.Name: Control Quality
Task.Notes: Measure and ensure that the project meets defined Quality Standards.

Task.Name: Participate in Testing
Task.Notes: Witness testing, conduct verification testing, and conduct acceptance testing of subcontracted components.

Task.Name: Measure Quality Levels
Task.Notes: Interpret project measurements as the basis for the continual improvement and optimization of work processes.

Task.Name: Manage Project Team
Task.Notes: Tracking team performance, providing feedback, resolving issues and coordinating changes to the team to ensure optimal project performance.

Task.Name: Manage Communications
Task.Notes: Develop and implement effective communications among all members of the project team.

Task.Name: Meet With Team
Task.Notes: Meet regularly with team members to review status, share experiences, provide suggestions, and resolve problems and concerns.

Task.Name: Monitor Team Morale
Task.Notes: Monitor team morale and take action to correct problem areas.

Task.Name: Conduct Team Performance Reviews
Task.Notes: Record and communicate the accomplishments of team members, and appraise their skills, to facilitate career development.

Task.Name: Produce Performance Reports
Task.Notes: Monitor and report on the costs, schedule, and technical performance of the project.

Task.Name: Report Weekly Status
Task.Notes: Summarize and communicate the accomplishments for the reporting period, the objectives for the coming period, problems (if any), the status of outstanding risk items, and suggestions for dealing with issues and problems.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Project Weekly Status Report, Risk Management Log, Project Tracking Summary Report, Action Items

Task.Name: Report Monthly Status
Task.Notes: Keep project status visible to Project Stakeholders by providing an appropriate summary of project status on a regular monthly basis.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Project Monthly Status Report, Action Items

Task.Name: Manage Stakeholders
Task.Notes: All project stakeholders must be effectively communicated to to ensure a common consistent view of the project exists. It is important to ensure that the project stakeholders are satisfied with the project results.

Task.Name: Monitor Satisfaction
Task.Notes: Monitor how well the stakeholder's expectations for quality service delivery are being met.

Task.Name: Resolve Issues
Task.Notes: Identify, track and resolve issues affecting the project.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Issue Resolution Request, Issue Log, Working Papers

Task.Name: Risk Monitoring and Control
Task.Notes: Managing the Risk Log and acting on Risk Management Action Plans as required to ensure the project stays on schedule.

Task.Name: Manage Risks
Task.Notes: Manage the Risk Log and the Risk Action plans to ensure that risks do not impact the project.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Risk Management Action Plan, Risk Management Log

Task.Name: Contract Administration
Task.Notes: Ensure that all contract terms and conditions, both buyer and seller, are adhered to during the life of the contract

Task.Name: Manage Subcontractor Contract
Task.Notes: Manage the relationship between the acquisition organization and the subcontracting organization.

ExtendedAttribute.Value: Acquisition Management Plan, Definition of Project Scope, Statement of Requirements, Statement of Work, Planning Budget, Planning Schedule, Contract Files, Subcontractor Payments

Task.Name: Closing
Task.Notes: Close out the project upon completion.

Task.Name: Close Project
Task.Notes: Make sure that the project is properly closed down, either when project delivery is complete or when the project is terminated for whatever reason.

Task.Name: Assess Satisfaction
Task.Notes: Document the overall satisfaction with the project.

Task.Name: Summarize Project Results and Lessons Learned
Task.Notes: Work with the project team to capture relevant experience and lessons learned for the benefit of future projects.

Task.Name: Review and Recognize Team Performance
Task.Notes: Complete performance reviews for each team member, recognize efforts and accomplishments, and celebrate success.

Task.Name: Close Out the Project Records
Task.Notes: Update and archive project documentation and make sure that all close out conditions have been met.

Task.Name: Review and Reconcile Financial Performance
Task.Notes: Make sure that all invoices have been delivered and all payments made.

Task.Name: Contract Closure
Task.Notes: Blab

Task.Name: Close Contract
Task.Notes: Specific actions required to ensure acceptance of deliverables, process final payments and archive and close out project contract files.

Resource.Name: Project Director
Resource.Notes: Responsible for management of the project at a strategic level.

Resource.Name: Project Manager
Resource.Notes: Responsible for the delivery of a quality project on-schedule, within budget, with a satisfied Acceptor and a motivated project team.

Resource.Name: Acceptor
Resource.Notes: Key individual within the business organization who is the principal interface with the project team and who has the authority to accept all deliverables and resolve all project issues (sometimes referred to as the Project Sponsor).

Resource.Name: Application Architect
Resource.Notes: Defines the major application systems needed to support the enterprise. During systems development, the Application Architect defines the application solution.

Resource.Name: Technical Architect
Resource.Notes: Defines the technologies and standards required to support the application and information architectures. During systems development, the Technical Architect defines the technical solution.

Resource.Name: Quality Assurance Manager
Resource.Notes: Responsible for providing confidence to management that the Quality System is being applied.

Resource.Name: Contracts Manager
Resource.Notes: Responsible for managing the contractual interfaces with the customer and with subcontractors.
